lout
====

This module handles output for other scripts in this directory

    >>> import l, lout
    >>> lout.argv.test_args('-h ')
    Usage: ... [options]
    <BLANKLINE>
    Options:
      -q, --quiet   hide directories, blank lines, ...
      -l, --lines   separate by returns (tabs is default)
      -i, --ignore  Do not ignore files (that subversion ignores)
      -h, --help    show this help message and exit

    >>> files = l.get_files()
    >>> files = l.remove_ignored(files)
    >>> names = l.get_names(files)
    >>> show( lout.format(names) )
    ['glob_path.py,test',
     'l.py,test,tests',
     'lout.py,test',
     'lx.py,test,tests',
     'ly.py,test']

    >>> lout.show(lout.format(names))
    glob_path.py,test l.py,test,tests   lout.py,test      lx.py,test,tests  ly.py,test        

    >>> lout.os.environ['COLUMNS'] = '60'
    >>> lout.show(lout.format(names))
    glob_path.py,test l.py,test,tests   lout.py,test      
    lx.py,test,tests  ly.py,test        

    >>> lout.os.environ['COLUMNS'] = '40'
    >>> lout.show(lout.format(names))
    glob_path.py,test l.py,test,tests   
    lout.py,test      lx.py,test,tests  
    ly.py,test        

    >>> lout.os.environ['COLUMNS'] = '80'
    >>> lout.argv.test_args('-l ')
    >>> lout.show(lout.format(names))
    glob_path.py,test 
    l.py,test,tests   
    lout.py,test      
    lx.py,test,tests  
    ly.py,test        
